<div class="quotetitle">NESter wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I'm not sure what the point would be now that there is a SNES Powerpak.<br /></div><br />I can think of several reasons.<br /><ul><li>Price competition </li><li>Regulatory competition (for example, anything made in Brazil is likely to be far cheaper for people in Brazil to buy due to Brazil's import duty) </li><li>Feature competition </li><li>Ship date competition (ability to ship while competitor's product is out of stock) </li></ul><br />Case in point: SuperCard DS One and CycloDS Evolution still sold, despite R4 producing a microSD adapter for DS first, because they offered different features and may have been in stock when a retailer was out of R4 cards.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Jul 22, 2010 10:18 am</p><hr />
