<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5529&amp;p=50273#p50273</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5529&amp;p=50273#p50273"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Theoretical SNES flash cart idea]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5529&amp;p=50273#p50273"><![CDATA[
What about sticking a GBA SuperCard inside a cartridge, converting the voltage, and hoping it works?<br />Obviously you'd need a mapper, because the 32MB address space is too big, and there would need to be a way to switch the supercard bewteen BIOS/IO mode and RAM mode.  Can't do that without twiddling the highest address bits.<br />Probably would also need a custom BIOS which would run SNES code instead of GBA code.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri Aug 28, 2009 7:15 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
